The paper deals with the Efficient Domination problem in chordal graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and its solvability in polynomial time, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.CG). Finally, the paper focuses on specific subclasses of chordal graphs, such as net, extended gem, and $S_{1,2,3}$-free graphs, which are topics in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT).
